hods at 10,", "bbox": [199.0, 746.2, 708.4, 762.1]}, {"text": "30, 60 and 120 mins annealing times.", "bbox": [199.0, 759.3, 366.5, 774.9]}, {"text": "Tensile testing. The films prepared by the two film preparation methods were sliced into strips with the", "bbox": [198.9, 804.1, 708.7, 819.6]}, {"text": "width of 3 mm and length of 6 cm. The gauge length of the strip is 2.5 mm. The tensile tests were performed on", "bbox": [198.9, 816.9, 708.9, 832.4]}, {"text": "a Lloyds EZ20 machine with a crosshead speed of 20 mm min−1 for all samples. The test were repeated ten times", "bbox": [198.9, 829.6, 709.0, 845.2]}, {"text": "for each type of sample.", "bbox": [198.9, 842.4, 306.3, 857.9]}, {"text": "Thermal analysis DSC. Mettler Toledo DSC 821e/700 was used to carry out thermal analysis. The quenched", "bbox": [198.9, 865.4, 708.8, 881.0]}, {"text": "crystallised and melt crystallised film samples were heated in DSC from 50 °C to 450 °C at a heating rate of 10 °C", "bbox": [198.9, 878.2, 708.9, 893.7]}, {"text": "min−1 under nitrogen atmosphere at a flow rate of 50 ml min−1. The test were repeated three times for each type of", "bbox": [198.9, 891.0, 709.0, 906.5]}, {"text": "sample. % crystallinity values of the PEEK films fabricated using the two crystallisation methods were calculated", "bbox": [198.9, 903.8, 708.9, 919.3]}, {"text": "using the equation below:", "bbox": [198.9, 916.6, 316.1, 932.1]}, {"text": "SCiEntifiC REPORts | (2018) 8:1314 | DOI:10.1038/s41598-018-19537-1 5", "bbox": [52.1, 964.7, 708.9, 979.9]}]}